15 "§407.29.1. Provisional eligibility; child care assistance program application
16 A. An expectant mother may apply for assistance from the Child Care
17 Assistance Program, through the Department of Education, prior to birth of the
18 child in order to preliminarily determine whether the applicant will be eligible.
19 B. The department shall develop a process to determine provisional
20 eligibility of an applicant and to later confirm eligibility after the birth of the
21 child. The process shall be subject to approval by the Senate and House
22 committees on education, jointly.
23 C. The department shall promulgate rules and regulations in accordance
24 with the Administrative Procedure Act as necessary for the implementation of
25 this Section."
